    "pathophysiology": [
      "C. tetani (gram-positive anaerobe) produces tetanospasmin toxin",
      "Toxin undergoes retrograde axonal transport, cleaves synaptobrevin to block GABA/glycine release",
      "Loss of inhibition causes unopposed motor activity → rigidity and autonomic instability"
